      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation on three systematically refined meshes yields discretization error estimate below 5% on hemolysis index at all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M cells) used for Richardson extrapolation. Estimated discretization error on normalized hemolysis index ranges 6–9% across operating points, exceeding the 5% threshold. Achieved level (2) falls below required level (3); gap documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
